57.description:
STON.fi is a decentralized exchange (DEX) built on TON Blockchain smart contracts, enhanced with advantages such as low fees, low slippage, super user-friendly interface and direct integration with the TON wallet.
STON.fi is a peer-to-peer trading platform where transactions are conducted directly between crypto-traders, and do not require third-party participation.
STON.fi:
implements one of the main features of cryptocurrencies — it facilitates financial transactions without any involvement of banks, brokers or any other traditional intermediaries;
utilizes the TON blockchain and is a natural part of TON DeFi’s growing suite of tools that make a huge range of financial services available directly from the TON cryptocurrency wallet.
We are looking for a new frontend team member who will be immersed in the process of working with TON Blockchain and its unique features; will help the present team in bringing new complicated business scenarios to life and upgrading the current application.
Responsibilities:
Producing typescript code that is easy to read, testable, supported, and framework independent;
Building interfaces with the react framework, scss, storybook, component driven development, and mobile first approaches;
Writing unit test using jest/vitest, e2e and integration tests using cypress;
Application performance optimization: profiling, analysis and reduction of problem spots, refactoring;
Immersion in the context of business requirements and operation of the application scenarios; communication in an open community of users and partner developers.
Requirements:
Strong knowledge of javascript (ES6+), typescript;
Ability to make adaptive interfaces using css/sass;
Expertise with the react framework and its ecosystem (react-router, react-hook-forms, react-testing-library).
Desired Bonus Skills:
Knowledge of the frameworks Next.js, svelete, and mobs state manager;
Expertise with themization and localization implementation;
Experience in developing and supporting CI/CD workflows with gitlab and docker;
Maintaining versioned application releases in git and expertise working with git flow for version control.
Ston.fi is an equal opportunity employer.
Salary and compensation
No salary data published by company so we estimated salary based on similar jobs related to React, JavaScript, Git, Typescript, Mobile, Senior and Digital Nomad jobs that are similar:
$70,000 — $120,000/year
Location
Worldwide

64.description:
At Utrust we're looking for Roles in these teams: Software Engineering and Product Development.
At Utrust, we’re looking for passionate people that share our mission, vision, and values; and want to make a change in the industry. Are you ready for the challenge? 😉 Read the description below and apply to be part of our fantastic team! 🙌
About the job
We are looking for committed and passionate people to join our Product team. We need someone as passionate as us about changing the world with crypto and also passionate about design-focused development. If that’s you, and a fast-paced environment doesn’t scare you, help us scale a product that will bridge the gap between crypto buyers and leading companies across the world. 😎
What we need:
5+ years of experience in an Engineering team;
Knowledge of Agile development methodology;
A willingness to deal with unexpected problems (we are scaling up, you see).
Strong decision making skills (our platform is still in its early stages, so a lot of the technical decisions are still in the making, and you will be a part of that);
Experience within a startup or FinTech;
A healthy respect for security. We practice and follow security and privacy by design.
What would be great:
Full Stack Developer:
Experience in leading the architecture definition of products and teams;
Proficiency with Elixir Umbrella App and CQRS/Event sourcing approach;
Knowledge of Phoenix framework;
Experience of writing & maintaining test automation at unit / integration / component level;
Experience with EEx views and React, Ajax and Web Sockets;
Backend Developer:
3+ years of experience with Blockchain technologies - such as integrating with different blockchains (Bitcoin, Ethereum, Elrond, etc.).
Knowledge of Typescript and NodeJS;
Experience developing Dapps in Solidity or similar;
Knowledge of L2 technologies such as StarkNet, ZKSync and Arbitrum;
Product Manager:
Good understanding of customers’ problems and needs. Your goal is driving the process to create something that will let them succeed at what they’re trying to do;
Experience defining and prioritizing product features;
Strong problem-solving skills and willingness to roll up one’s sleeves to get the job - nobody said it was easy!
QA Engineer:
Strong knowledge and extensive practical experience in software testing and quality assurance;
Strong understanding of manual testing techniques;
Hands-on experience implementing test automation frameworks across different test levels specially written in JavaScript and experience with frameworks such as Selenium, Cypress, Jest, Jasmine, etc;
DevSecOps:
Maintain and optimize AWS-based infrastructure, and ensure it is ready to scale;
Designing, implementing and maintaining CI/CD workflows - currently Github Actions;
Run/organize internal security audits and prepare for external ones;
Extensive experience with AWS Cloud services such as IAM, ECS & RDS;
Engineering Team Lead:
Management experience of an engineering team for at least 2 years;
Drive to create a culture of communication, quality, agility and high performance;
Focus on efficient processes with a kind, people-first approach;
What we offer: 🤩
An incredible and passionate team of experienced people that share the passion for disruptive technology and vision of a new digital payments landscape;
Remote friendly culture;
Flexible work schedule (we want you to accomplish the best work of your life - that means working to your strengths, and adjusting your own working hours);
Onboarding kit;
Growth Budget (we support our team’s growth);
Company Culture (We aren’t just another fintech company. We really want to change the world. Our people is our main priority. We have values, and we take them seriously);
Internal Projects (all our team is encouraged to be proactive and to start and work on independent projects. Focus on growth. Focus on impact.);
Company paid retreats;
Training sessions;
All-hands sessions and heartbeat communication (We put our people first. These are 100% transparent and we want everyone to participate.) 
Sounds like you? Great! 😎
If you feel like you don’t know every single technology listed here, don’t despair. As long as you’re willing to learn, we will mentor you.
Want to know some insights from the Product Team before you apply? Check here!
Apply for the job
Do you want to join our Product or Engineering team? Then we'd love to hear about you!
Salary and compensation
No salary data published by company so we estimated salary based on similar jobs related to Solidity, Crypto, Testing, JavaScript, Cloud and Typescript jobs that are similar:
$67,500 — $120,000/year
Location
Remote (Within European timezones)
